        </div>
        <div class="input-group">
          <label>Expected Move / IV (%)</label>
          <input type="number" id="calcVol" value="25" min="0" step="0.1" />
        </div>
        <button class="btn-calc" id="btnCalcRange" type="button">Calculate</button>
      </div>
      <div class="result-box" id="rangeResult">
        <div class="result-row"><span class="result-label">1-Day Expected Range (±1σ)</span><span class="result-val" id="res1d"></span></div>
        <div class="result-row"><span class="result-label">1-Week Expected Range (±1σ)</span><span class="result-val" id="res1w"></span></div>
        <div class="result-row"><span class="result-label">1-Month Expected Range (±1σ)</span><span class="result-val" id="res1m"></span></div>
        <div class="result-row"><span class="result-label">Daily Move ($)</span><span class="result-val" id="resDailyMove"></span></div>
        <div class="result-row"><span class="result-label">Weekly Move ($)</span><span class="result-val" id="resWeeklyMove"></span></div>
        <div class="result-row"><span class="result-label">Monthly Move ($)</span><span class="result-val" id="resMonthlyMove"></span></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- HV vs IV Comparison -->
  <div class="section" id="hv-iv-comparison">
    <h2>Historical vs Implied Volatility Comparison</h2>
    <p>Compare a stock's historical volatility with its current implied volatility to see if options are trading at a premium or discount. When IV exceeds HV, options are considered expensive — a signal for options sellers.</p>
    <div class="tool-card">
      <h3>&#128202; IV Premium/Discount Analyzer</h3>
      <div class="input-row">
        <div class="input-group">
          <label>Historical Volatility (%)</label>
          <input type="number" id="inputHV" value="20" min="0" step="0.1" />
        </div>
        <div class="input-group">
          <label>Implied Volatility (%)</label>
